valid: returns true if a value is valid for the given type (whether a number is finite, whether a color is displayable, etc.)
firstvalid: returns the first value which is valid for its type (the first finite number, the first color which is displayable, etc.)
and: returns true if both inputs are true
or: returns true if either of its inputs are true
π: ratio of any circle's circumference to its diameter
τ: ratio of any circle's circumference to its radius
∞: limit as a number increases without bound
+: unary plus; ensures a numeric value is passed
↑: raises a value to an exponent
arg: returns the angle between a point and the x-axis
conj: takes the conjugate of a complex number or quaternion
imag: gets the imaginary part of a complex number
real: gets the real part of a multi-dimensional number
sign: gets the sign of a number
dot: takes the dot product of two complex numbers
complex: converts a point into a complex number
point: constructs a point from multi-dimensional values
.i: gets the coefficient of 'i' in a multi-dimensional number
cplot: gets the color a complex number would be represented by when performing domain coloring
cplothue: gets the hue a complex number would be represented by when performing domain coloring
p: coordinates of currently drawn shader pixel
i: unit vector perpendicular to number line; a square root of -1
erf: error function; related to area of a normal distribution
min: returns the minimum of its inputs
max: returns the maximum of its inputs
total: returns the sum of its inputs
mean: takes the arithmetic mean of its inputs
median: takes the median of its inputs
quartile: computes a quartile of a data set
quantile: computes a quantile of a data set or the inverse CDF of a distribution
ranks: computes the rank of each element of a list
center: gets the center of a circle
circle: constructs a circle from a center and radius
distance: calculates the distance between two objects
end: gets the ending point of a vector
glider: constructs a point on an object
intersection: constructs the point where two objects intersect
line: constructs a line between two points
midpoint: constructs the midpoint of a line segment or between two points
parallel: creates a line parallel to an existing line which passes through some point
perpendicular: creates a line perpendicular to an existing line which passes through some point
polygon: constructs a polygon from a set of points
radius: measures the radius of a circle
ray: constructs a ray (a line going in a particular direction)
segments: gets the segments which make up a polygon
start: gets the starting point of a vector
vector: constructs a vector between two points
vertices: gets the vertices which make up a polygon
angle: constructs an angle from three vertices
directed angle: constructs an angle with a particular direction
angles: constructs an angle at every vertex of a polygon
directed angles: constructs a directed angle at every vertex of a polygon
angle bisector: constucts the bisector of an angle
perpendicular bisector: constucts the perpendicular bisector of a line segment or between two points
arc: constructs an arc from three points
length: calculates the length of an object
translate: translates an object by a vector
rotate: rotates an object around a point by some angle
dilate: scales an object from some point by some scaling factor
reflect: reflects an object across a line
perimeter: measures the perimeter of a polygon
join: joins multiple lists into a single one
sort: sorts the elements of a list
unique: removes any duplicate elements in a list
forceshader: forces the given expression to be executed in a shader
x: x-coordinate of currently drawn shader pixel
y: y-coordinate of currently drawn shader pixel
forcejs: evaluates an expression outside a shader, then passes the value to the shader
imgwidth: gets the natural width of an image
imgheight: gets the natural height of an image
imgaspect: gets the preferred aspect ratio of an image
intosi: converts a value to its component SI units
unit: returns the unit with a given symbol
concat: concatenates one or more string-like values into a string
base: interprets numbers in <lhs> as if they were in base <rhs>
eldiscoveredby: gets the discoverer of an element
elname: gets the name of an element
elappearance: gets the appearance of an element
elcategory: gets the category of an element
elphase: gets the phase of an element at STP
eldescription: gets a description of an element
elsymbol: gets the symbol of an element
elconfig: gets the electron configuration of an element
elconfigshort: gets the electron configuration of an element using the noble gas shorthand
elblock: gets the block an element is in on the periodic table
mass: gets the mass of an element
eleaffinity: amount of energy released when an electron attaches to a neutral atom of this element
elenegativity: tendency for an atom of an element to attract shared electrons in a chemical bond
elmolarheat: amount of energy required to increase the temperature of one mole of an element by one degree kelvin
elperiod: period of an element in the periodic table
element: returns the element with a given symbol
debugast: returns the AST of its input
image: draws an image on the graphpaper; pass a number to override the preferred aspect ratio
ithkuil script: converts an ithkuil word into script form
ithkuil values: given the name of a grammatical category of ithkuil, returns all values it can take
ithkuil valid: checks if a consonant form is valid according to ithkuil phonotactics
ithkuil valid initial: checks if a consonant form is valid word-initially according to ithkuil phonotactics
ithkuil valid final: checks if a consonant form is valid word-finally according to ithkuil phonotactics
ithkuil ca: generates an ithkuil CA form, optionally geminated
ithkuil all: list of all grammatical categories in ithkuil
unsign: takes the absolute value of the components of a value
.j: gets the coefficient of 'j' in a quaternion
.k: gets the coefficient of 'k' in a quaternion
j: a four-dimensional unit vector perpendicular to 1, i, and k
k: a four-dimensional unit vector perpendicular to 1, i, and j
slopefield: generates a slope or vector field
unsym: interpolates a value into a symbolic expression
eval: evaluates a symbolic expression in the current evaluation context
